Concentration dynamics of a pollutant in a fluid with fuzzy propagation velocity by Zadeh’s Extension Principle

Matheus Saraiva Alcino, Silvio Antônio Bueno Salgado, Danilo Machado Pires, Sérgio Martins de Souza, Robson André Armindo, Nilton César da Silva

The C++ algorithm

The algorithm was written in C++ language using standard libraries. 

#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <cmath>
#include <iomanip>
#include <stdio.h>
#include <vector>
#include <algorithm>

In this study the main idea is to allow the Zadeh extension principle to be applied to the expression (12) related to the pollutant concentration along the pipe.

\(u(x,t)=f(x-ct)=\frac{1}{2\sqrt{\pi}}e^{-\frac{1}{4}(x-ct)^2}\)

Assuming \(c\) as a triangular fuzzy number that models the pollutant propagation velocity such that

where \([a_1,a_2,a_3]\) is the inf, pic and sup values, i.e., the smallest, the avarage (maximum membership) and the largest values of \(c\) respectively.

Since \([c]^{\alpha}=[c_{-}^{\alpha}; c_{+}^{\alpha}]\) \(\forall~ \alpha \in [0,1]\) we have \([u(x,t)]^\alpha=[min f(s), max f(s)]\) where \(s \in [x-c_{-}^{\alpha}t,x-c_{+}^{\alpha}t]\).

In summary the algorithm consists of the following steps

  • It was defined a data structure able to memorize 3 double values type, which correspond to \(x\), \(u(x,t)\) e \(\mu(c)\).
using namespace std;
struct trinca{
       long double valorx, valorfx, valorp;
};

A variable of that type will be used to memorize values related in the matrix form, for exemple

\(x=30\) \(u(x=30,t=10)\) \(\mu(c)\)
30 0.000000000000000 0.0
30 0.000000000000000 0.1
… … …
30 0.000000000000007 0.4
30 0.000000000000021 0.5
30 0.000000000000061 0.6
… … …
30 0.000000000003918 1
… … …
30 0.000000000182274 0.6
30 0.000000000452826 0.5
30 0.000000001102691 0.4
… … …
30 0.000000014122280 0.1
30 0.000000031745587 0.0

It is important to notice that even when \(x\) and \(t\) are constants we have differents values of \(u(x,t)\), because the velocity \(c\) is still varying. Furthermore, the different merberships atributed to the distinct values of \(c\) are the ones wich wil be extended to \(u(x,t)\).

Three support functions were generated to the extension principle process:

  • The sorting function: consists in to taking the values of matrix (array) generated in each point (exemple above) according to \(u(x,t)\)
void ordenacao(vector < trinca > &vet)
{ 
     
    double b,i;
           trinca orden;
       
        b=1;
         while (b<vet.size())
        {
               orden.valorx = vet[b].valorx;
               orden.valorfx =vet[b].valorfx;
                 orden.valorp = vet[b].valorp;
           
           i = (b-1);
          while((i>=0)&&(vet[i].valorfx > orden.valorfx))
         {
             vet[i+1] = vet[i];
                    i = (i - 1);
        }
            vet[i+1]=orden;
        b+=1;
            }
          

}

  • Since the data is already sorted a function called exentension principle is executed. This function verifies if it exists repeated values of \(u(x,t)\) and deletes the one that presents the smallest merbership.

void principioextencao(vector<trinca> &vet)
{ 
     int i,j;
    
     j=1;
     
     while(j<vet.size())
    {   
       i = (j-1);
           if((vet[j].valorfx)==(vet[i].valorfx))
         {  
                    if(vet[j].valorp>=vet[i].valorp)
                     { 
                    
                        vet.erase(vet.begin()+i);
                     }
                     else
                             {
                         
                         vet.erase(vet.begin()+j);
                         
                      }
            continue;   
         }j+=1;
         
    }
       
 }

  • Finally, there is the center of gravity function, which consists of the fuzzy set defuzzification step.

long double centroide (vector<trinca> &veto)
{
     long double numerador,denominador,c;
     numerador=0.0;
     denominador=0.0;
      c=0.0;
 while(c<=(veto.size()))

    { 
          numerador+=(veto[c].valorp)*(veto[c].valorfx);
          denominador+=veto[c].valorp;       
     c+=1.0; }
   
   return (numerador/denominador);

}

Because of some particularities of the C language, some “holes” arises after the execution of the “principioextencao” function in some extreme points of the fuzzy \(u(x,t)\) graph. We usually denominate that problem as noises, and this is adjusted by removing those points wich cause such noises. For example

void convexo(vector<trinca> &vet)
{        double i,j,l;
    j,l=1;

         while (l<(vet.size()-1.0))
           {
             i=j-1; l=j+1;
             if( (vet[i].valorp>=vet[j].valorp)&&(vet[j].valorp<=vet[l].valorp))
                    {       vet.erase(vet.begin()+j);
            
                    j=1;
              l=1;
                      continue;

                    }
                 
          j+=1;
        }

}

At the end of the execution three files are generated:

  • aposalgoritmo.gnu: contains the fuzzy set resulting from the extension principle, \(x\), \(u(x,t)\) e \(\mu(u(x,t))\).
  • sclassica.gnu : contains the values of \(t\), \(x\) e \(u(x,t)\), from the classic function.
  • classica.gnu : contains the values of \(x\) e \(u(x,t)\), from the classic function.
  • defu.gnu : contains the deffuzificated values of \(\mu(u(x,t))\) for each point of \(x\).
ofstream convex("./aposalgoritmo.gnu", ios::out);
ofstream borrao("./sclassica.gnu", ios::out);
ofstream cla("./classica.gnu", ios::out);
ofstream defuzzy("./defu.gnu", ios::out);
int main()
{

  vector < trinca > vetorPonto; 
  trinca armazena0,armazena1,armazena2;     
 
 long double  pon,c,inf, sup, z,r,t,x,x1,u1,u2,u0,al,pic;
const  double d= 1;

// The parameters a1,a2 and a3 for the fuzzy number c
cout<<" Enter the lower range, the peak and the upper range of the triangular membership: "<<endl;
cin>>inf; cin>>pic; cin>>sup;
// The moment   
cout<<" Enter time: "<<endl;
cin>>t;
// pipe length
cout<<"  Enter the lower and the upper limit of the pipe: "<<endl;
cin>>x; cin>>x1;

    
            // Initial point in the pipe.
        while(x<=x1)  
        {         
          al=0;
          while (al<=0.99)  //  Length of the whole, in this case (<80)
                  {
//[min f(s)]         
              u1= (1/sqrt(4*d*M_PI))*exp((-0.25/d)*(x-((pic-inf)*al+inf)*t)*(x-((pic-inf)*al+inf)*t));
                    armazena1.valorx = x;
                            armazena1.valorfx =u1;
                            armazena1.valorp = al;
                            vetorPonto.push_back(armazena1);
//[max f(s)]    
                            u2= (1/sqrt(4*d*M_PI))*exp((-0.25/d )*(x-((pic-sup)*al+sup)*t)*(x-((pic-sup)*al+sup)*t));
                            armazena2.valorx = x;
                            armazena2.valorfx =u2;
                            armazena2.valorp = al;
                            vetorPonto.push_back(armazena2);
                                        
                        al+=0.01;
                            
              } 

//  u(x,t) classic, membership equal to 1
          z=(1/sqrt(d*4*M_PI))*exp((-0.25/d)*(x-pic*t)*(x-pic*t));    
          armazena0.valorx = x;
          armazena0.valorfx = z ;
            armazena0.valorp = 1;
          vetorPonto.push_back(armazena0);
            
// Stores classic function data (3d)  t, x , u(x,t)                            
                    borrao<<setiosflags(ios::fixed| ios:: showpoint)<<setprecision(15.0);
          borrao<<t<<" "<<x<<" "<<z<<endl;
          
// Stores classic function data (2d) x e u(x,t)            
          cla<<setiosflags(ios::fixed| ios:: showpoint)<<setprecision(15.0);
          cla<<x<<" "<<z<<endl;
          
// Sorts data according to u(x,t)
          ordenacao(vetorPonto);   
          
// More relevance 
          principioextencao(vetorPonto); 
                
//  Defuzzification
                    r=centroide(vetorPonto);

// Stores defuzzified data                                
          defuzzy<<setiosflags(ios::fixed| ios:: showpoint)<<setprecision(15.0);
          defuzzy<<x<<" "<<r<<endl;
          
// Eliminates "noise"                          
            convexo(vetorPonto);
            
 // Storage of fuzzy u(x,t)    
          convex<<setiosflags(ios::fixed| ios:: showpoint)<<setprecision(15);
        
            for (int v=0;v<vetorPonto.size();v++)
               {
               convex<<vetorPonto[v].valorx<<" "<<vetorPonto[v].valorfx<<" "<<vetorPonto[v].valorp<<endl;
             }
                  convex<<" "<<endl;
          
          
          vetorPonto.clear();
                    
              x+=0.01;
                 
         }
               
    
 return 0;
}
